0consumer%20and%20federal%20spending.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Zandi%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Moody's%20Analytics%2C%20tells%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he's%20still%20harboring%20reservations%20about%20how%20things%20are%20going%20under%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20has%20been%20ringing%20the%20alarm%20on%20the%20economy%20all%20year%2C%20recently%20stating%20that%20he%20saw%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-recession-economy-tariffs-immigration-policy-jobs-data-bls-trump-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20GDP%20report%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20have%20restored%20his%20confidence%20that%20better%20days%20are%20ahead.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20the%20big%20gain%20in%20real%20GDP%20growth%20in%20the%20quarter%2C%20underlying%20real%20GDP%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20abstracting%20from%20the%20quarterly%20vagaries%20of%20the%20data%20%E2%80%94%20is%20closer%20to%202%25%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20but%20not%20great%2C%20and%20not%20strong%20enough%20to%20create%20enough%20jobs%2C%20as%20unemployment%20is%20steadily%20moving%20higher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20was%20predicting%20a%203.8%25%20increase%20in%20real%20GDP%20growth%2C%20higher%20than%20most%20economists'%20estimates%20of%203.3%25.%20As%20such%2C%20he%20isn't%20surprised%20by%20the%20numbers%2C%20although%20he%20also%20speculated%20that%20the%20big%20upside%20surprise%20may%20have%20been%20driven%20by%20technical%20quirks%20as%20opposed%20to%20actual%20momentum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20difference%20with%20my%20forecast%20is%20the%20more%20substantial%20narrowing%20of%20the%20trade%20deficit%2C%20but%20this%20is%20due%20to%20the%20swings%20caused%20by%20the%20tariffs.%20Government%20spending%20was%20also%20stronger%2C%20but%20this%20is%20likely%20due%20to%20a%20measurement%20issue%2C%26q