%20compared%20to%20adoption%20rates%20for%20personal%20computers%20(19.7%25)%20and%20the%20internet%20(30.1%25)%20three%20years%20after%20they%20were%20widely%20introduced%2C%20according%20to%20research%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fon-the-economy%2F2025%2Fnov%2Fstate-generative-ai-adoption-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20about%2021%25%20of%20US%20workers%20say%20that%20at%20least%20some%20of%20their%20job%20is%20now%20done%20with%20AI%2C%20an%20increase%20from%2016%25%20roughly%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2025%2F10%2F06%2Fabout-1-in-5-us-workers-now-use-ai-in-their-job-up-since-last-year%2F%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20transforming%20everything%20about%20work%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-jobs-ai-creates-workforce-decision-designer-experience-officer-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20jobs%20people%20do%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20how%20they%20do%20them.%20Organizations%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20are%20racing%20to%20prepare%20their%20people%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-improving-workplace-how-to-use-ai-identify-skill-gaps-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20comes%20next%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20long-term%20impact%20remains%20uncertain%2C%20early%20patterns%20are%20emerging%20about%20what's%20working%20and%20what%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22895ae212-eb65-40f5-aa5f-6c09b40dc5e2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20job%20titles%2C%20big%20expectations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAI's%20effect%20on%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20showing%20up%20everywhere%3A%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-interview-ai-bot-hr-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20companies%20screen%20candidates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20skills%20command%20premium%20salaries%2C%20and%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbcg-head-of-people-ai-core-competencies-performance-evaluations-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20gets%20evaluated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Two%20structural%20shifts%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20stand%20out%3A%20new%20jobs%20are%20emerging%2C%20and%20old%20jobs%20are%20evolving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20authoritative%20count%20of%20new%20AI-specific%20job%20titles%20is%20hard%20to%20come%20by%2C%20but%20data%20show%20rapid%20growth.%20A%20report%20from%20software%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadsknews.autodesk.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fai-jobs-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAutodesk%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20demand%20for%20roles%20like%20AI%20engineer%20jumped%20143.2%25%20in%202024%2C%20while%20prompt%20engineer%20rose%20135.8%25%2C%20and%20AI%20content%20creator%20increased%20134.5%25.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20requiring%20AI%20skills%20rose%207.5%25%20last%20year%2C%20even%20as%20total%20job%20postings%20fell%2011.3%25%2C%20according%20to%20research%20from%20consultancy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pwc.com%2Fgx%2Fen%2Fissues%2Fartificial-intelligence%2Fjob-barometer%2F2025%2Freport.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPwC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMolly%20Roenna%2C%20global%20chief%20people%20officer%20at%20PR%20firm%20Weber%20Shandwick%2C%20sees%20this%20firsthand.%20Her%20company%20is%20increasingly%20seeking%20specialists%20in%20areas%20like%20AI%20integration%20and%20AI%20ethics%2C%20and%20it's%20recruiting%20from%20disciplines%20like%20behavioral%20science%20and%20data%20analytics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223014%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Molly%20Sands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945ca4d04eda4732f2deb5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222261%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMolly%20Sands%20is%20the%20head%20of%20the%20teamwork%20lab%20at%20Atlassian.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20Courtesy%20of%20Molly%20Sands%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20hiring%20for%20a%20fundamentally%20different%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Roenna%20says.%20%26quot%3BMeeting%20client%20expectations%20requires%20people%20who%20use%20technology%20as%20a%20force%20multiplier%20for%20insight%20and%20creativity%2C%20not%20just%20a%20shortcut%20for%20efficiency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hiring%20process%20itself%20has%20evolved%2C%20too.%20Many%20of%20Weber%20Shandwick's%20interviews%20now%20include%20a%20%26quot%3Btechnology%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpartner-with-ai-to-get-hired-and-win-job-interview-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20practice%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20appears%20to%20be%20gaining%20traction.%20This%20isn't%20to%20test%20technical%20skills%2C%20but%20to%20gauge%20how%20candidates%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20have%20they%20built%20with%20AI%3F%20What%20excites%20or%20worries%20them%20about%20it%3F%20We%20want%20perspective%20that%20comes%20from%20actual%20practice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dynamic%20playing%20out%20at%20Weber%20Shandwick%20and%20elsewhere%20isn't%20new.%20After%20all%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-officially-entered-quantum-era-major-advancements-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevery%20major%20technological%20advancement%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20created%20roles%20that%20were%20previously%20unimaginable%2C%20made%20others%20obsolete%2C%20and%20forced%20still%20others%20to%20adapt.%20What's%20different%20about%20this%20AI-driven%20era%2C%20however%2C%20is%20both%20the%20speed%20of%20change%20(see%20above)%20and%20the%20breadth%2C%20affecting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-entry-level-jobs-most-at-risk-ai-economist-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkers%20across%20industries%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-entry-level-jobs-most-at-risk-ai-economist-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskill%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20have%20programmers%20before%20computers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Esteve%20Almirall%20Mezquita%2C%20professor%20of%20data%2C%20analytics%2C%20technology%20and%20AI%20at%20Esade%20in%20Madrid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22396c26cd-2135-4e02-ba9c-30bf40ec2984%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESetting%20the%20goals%20for%20widespread%20use%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20new%20roles%20and%20demand%20for%20expertise%20is%20half%20the%20equation.%20The%20bigger%20challenge%20is%20helping%20existing%20workers%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20aren't%20leaving%20that%20to%20chance.%20They're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-workers-use-ai-survey-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequiring%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20notes%20Dan%20Schawbel%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Workplace%20Intelligence%2C%20a%20research%20firm.%20%26quot%3BCEOs%20are%20under%20enormous%20pressure%20to%20have%20their%20AI%20story%20intact%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20have%20our%20workers%20using%20AI.%20It's%20good%20for%20productivity%2C%20yes%2C%20but%20also%20our%20story%20and%20bottom%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-internal-memo-using-ai-no-longer-optional-github-copilot-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoinbase-ceo-fired-employees-not-using-ai-tools-onboarding-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoinbase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshopify-ceo-tobi-lutke-employees-prove-ai-job-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShopify%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20mandate%20AI%20use%2C%20according%20to%20previous%20reporting%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-employee-performance-review-overhaul-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20plans%20to%20measure%20employees'%20performance%20by%20their%20%26quot%3BAI-driven%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchawbel%20predicts%20more%20scrutiny%20in%20the%20year%20ahead.%20Employees%20will%20need%20to%20function%20like%20data%20scientists%2C%20continuously%20proving%20their%20value%2C%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhether%20you're%20in%20marketing%2C%20IT%2C%20or%20HR%2C%20every%20action%20can%20be%20measured%20and%20tracked%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20even%20tied%20directly%20to%20your%20compensation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb839786-9973-4e77-856d-06d7f2b34884%5C%22%3ETracking%20the%20ROI%20of%20AI%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeasuring%20AI%20use%20and%20seeing%20value%20from%20it%20are%20two%20different%20things%2C%20however.%20Even%20as%20organizations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-finally-paying-ai-cio-survey-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epour%20billions%20into%20the%20technology%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20results%20have%20been%20uneven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-publications.bcg.com%2FThe-Widening-AI-Value-Gap-October-2025.pdf%23page%3D11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20by%20consulting%20firm%20BCG%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20more%20than%201%2C250%20firms%20worldwide%20reports%20that%2060%25%20of%20companies%20are%20investing%20heavily%20in%20AI%20but%20seeing%20minimal%20returns.%20Meanwhile%2C%20only%205%25%20have%20taken%20the%20step%20to%20restructure%20their%20operations%20around%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20and%20those%20companies%20are%20seeing%20significant%20revenue%20gains%20over%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%2C%20the%20BCG%20research%20suggests%2C%20comes%20down%20to%20several%20factors.%20Successful%20companies%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-more-confident-that-their-ai-investments-will-pay-off-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy-in%20from%20the%20top%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20have%20redesigned%20how%20work%20gets%20done.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20says%20Alicia%20Pittman%2C%20BCG's%20global%20people%20chair%2C%20they've%20invested%20in%20teaching%20employees%20to%20use%20AI%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alicia%20Pittman%20sitting%20on%20a%20couch%20in%20black%20outfit%20and%20gold-colored%20necklace.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945ca8104eda4732f2deb63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224098%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlicia%20Pittman%2C%20Chief%20People%20Officer%2C%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%3Cp%3EBoston%20Consulting%20Group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPittman%20notes%20that%20industries%20like%20financial%20services%2C%20insurance%2C%20and%20healthcare%20are%20pulling%20ahead%20in%20AI%20adoption.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20companies%20put%20real%20time%20and%20energy%20into%20this%20in%20a%20way%20that%20hasn't%20been%20present%20before%2C%20and%20that's%20good%20for%20everybody%20and%20good%20for%20the%20global%20workforce.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGranted%2C%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-kills-jobs-paychecks-human-purpose-howard-marks-investor-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20displacement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20comes%20with%20that%20and%20some%20skill%20sets%20will%20go%20away%2C%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20helping%20people%20adapt%20to%20AI%20is%20a%20major%20investment%20in%20them%20as%20professionals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de41f5db-fc9f-4ed2-a2f1-0dc278237732%5C%22%3ETraining%20AI%20to%20work%20for%2C%20not%20instead%20of%2C%20humans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Moody's%2C%20the%20credit%20ratings%20firm%2C%20that%20investment%20involves%20encouraging%20employees%20to%20teach%20AI%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAri%20Lehavi%2C%20who%20runs%20applied%20AI%20there%2C%20says%20this%20approach%20frees%20employees%20to%20focus%20on%20complex%20work%20that%20requires%20human%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22819%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ari%20Lehavi%20in%20blue%20button%20shirt%20and%20black%20glasses%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945cb1704eda4732f2deb7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAri%20Lehavi%3Cp%3EAri%20Lehavi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20sales%2C%20for%20example.%20Customer%20relationship%20management%20(CRM)%20systems%20can%20capture%20basics%20like%20company%20size%2C%20contract%20history%2C%20and%20revenue%20potential.%20However%2C%20they%20miss%20what%20closes%20deals%3A%20company%20politics%2C%20individual%20motivations%2C%20and%20who%20really%20influences%20decisions.%20Lehavi's%20team%20teaches%20AI%20systems%20to%20learn%20those%20details%20so%20salespeople%20can%20concentrate%20on%20managing%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20can%20spend%20their%20time%20on%20things%20they're%20already%20doing%20but%20don't%20have%20enough%20time%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20hard%20cases%2C%20the%20edge%20cases%2C%20the%20complex%20situations%2C%20mentoring%20other%20people%2C%20management%2C%20and%20skill%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%3A%20the%20human%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20path%20forward%20isn't%20simple%20or%20straightforward.%20Not%20every%20company%20has%20the%20resources%20to%20retrain%20its%20workforce%2C%20and%20some%20jobs%20will%20indeed%20